text: Carlos Sablan Camacho (born February 27, 1937) was the first elected Governor of the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands, a commonwealth of the United States. He served as governor from January 9, 1978 through January 11, 1982. He was a member of the Democratic. Camacho was born in Saipan, Northern Mariana Islands. He studied at the University of Hawaii and at the Fiji School of Medicine. ==References== Category:1937 births Category:Living people Category:Governors of the Northern Mariana Islands Category:Democratic Party (United States) politicians Category:University of Hawaiʻi at Mānoa alumni
